\section{Numerical experiment in a simple case}
In order to verify the order of convergence in case of killed diffusion, let us perform a numerical experiment. We consider a two dimensional domain $D$ defined as
\begin{equation*}
	D = [-1,1]\times[-1,1], D \subset R^2.
\end{equation*}
We solve in the domain the following equation
\begin{equation}\label{eq:transport}
	\begin{cases}
		X(t) = -AX(t)dt + \sigma dW(t)\\
		X(0) = X_0, X_0 \in D
	\end{cases}
\end{equation}
Reference \cite{Gobet2001} provides a method for computing the expectation of the particle survival. Consider a domain $D\subset R^n$
